 {"id":"br-r37-c1-qtbp2","title":"parity: node_link_data/node_link_graph accepted positional source/target (kwarg-only in nx)","description":"fnx.node_link_data(G, 'from_', 'to_') worked but nx requires source/target/name/key/edges/nodes as keyword-only (the public signature uses '*,'). Symmetric defect on node_link_graph. Drop-in callers writing for nx wouldn't notice; callers writing for fnx and switching to nx would hit a TypeError. Hardened both signatures with '*,' so positional usage is rejected identically. Added tests/python/test_node_link_kwarg_only_parity.py with 5 cases pinning the contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:22:28.512465018Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:23:11.384386337Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:23:11.381244470Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit b739569. node_link_data and node_link_graph now require source/target/name/key/edges/nodes as keyword-only (matching nx). 5 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-qyx9u","title":"parity: top-level isomorphism module missing","description":"NetworkX exposes nx.isomorphism as a top-level module containing GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, ISMAGS, time-respecting matchers, match helper constructors, is_isomorphic, vf2pp_* helpers, and tree isomorphism helpers. FrankenNetworkX currently exports these names only at top level and lacks fnx.isomorphism / import franken_networkx.isomorphism. Add a module object backed by the FrankenNetworkX wrappers and register it in sys.modules, plus parity tests proving the module points at the wrapper classes/functions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:37:49.312623478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.985411035Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.983510716Z","close_reason":"Completed in 56128df","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-rnxtc","title":"parity: dag colliders/has_cycle/v_structures + structuralholes mutual_weight wrappers (5 functions)","description":"Five missing nx wrappers across two domains. DAG (causal graph helpers): colliders(G), has_cycle(G), v_structures(G). Structural holes (Burt 1992 weight helpers): mutual_weight(G, u, v, weight=None), normalized_mutual_weight(G, u, v, norm=sum, weight=None). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via _call_networkx_for_parity (top-level nx exports both directly), export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:27:40.051603203Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.729217982Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.727284532Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 674c3fc: 5 wrappers (has_cycle/colliders/v_structures/mutual_weight/normalized_mutual_weight) all verified against nx on DAG, Bayesian-net DAG, and weighted bidirectional DiGraph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-rygbm","title":"parity: align default-arg sentinels (stoer_wagner heap, capacity_scaling heap, adjacency_data attrs, trophic_* weight)","description":"Several fnx wrappers have None defaults where upstream nx uses concrete sentinel values, so default-arg introspection diverges. (1) stoer_wagner(G, weight, heap) — nx default heap=BinaryHeap class, fnx is None. (2) capacity_scaling(G, demand, capacity, weight, heap) — same heap default mismatch. (3) adjacency_data/adjacency_graph attrs — nx default {id: id, key: key} dict, fnx is None (so nx.adjacency_data(G) and fnx.adjacency_data(G) emit different JSON). (4) trophic_levels/trophic_differences/trophic_incoherence_parameter weight — nx default weight=weight, fnx is None (silently ignores edge weights by default). Align defaults; for heap=, accept None and substitute BinaryHeap so the public introspectable default matches nx; for trophic_*, change default to weight. for adjacency_data, default to nx attrs dict.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:22:48.044744102Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:22:48.044744102Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-rygbm","title":"parity: align default-arg sentinels (stoer_wagner heap, capacity_scaling heap, adjacency_data attrs, trophic_* weight)","description":"Several fnx wrappers have None defaults where upstream nx uses concrete sentinel values, so default-arg introspection diverges. (1) stoer_wagner(G, weight, heap) — nx default heap=BinaryHeap class, fnx is None. (2) capacity_scaling(G, demand, capacity, weight, heap) — same heap default mismatch. (3) adjacency_data/adjacency_graph attrs — nx default {id: id, key: key} dict, fnx is None (so nx.adjacency_data(G) and fnx.adjacency_data(G) emit different JSON). (4) trophic_levels/trophic_differences/trophic_incoherence_parameter weight — nx default weight=weight, fnx is None (silently ignores edge weights by default). Align defaults; for heap=, accept None and substitute BinaryHeap so the public introspectable default matches nx; for trophic_*, change default to weight. for adjacency_data, default to nx attrs dict.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:22:48.044744102Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:27:37.351954547Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:27:37.350109655Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit 3400846. All 7 functions now have nx-matching default-arg sentinels (BinaryHeap class for heap, mutable dict for attrs, 'weight' string for trophic_*). 12 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-s1gt6","title":"testing: parity smoke test for the 80 OrangeHorse wrappers (regression guard)","description":"OrangeHorse session shipped 13 beads adding ~80 nx-parity wrappers (TSP, approximation, bipartite, DAG, structuralholes, node_classification, RCM, random_sequence, tree.branchings, tree.mst, classes.filters, utils.heaps, frozen, coloring strategies, matching_dict_to_set, greedy_color callable fix). Add a parity smoke test (tests/python/test_orangehorse_parity_smoke.py) that for each of these symbols verifies (a) it is exported in fnx.__all__, (b) it is on fnx as an attribute, and (c) for callables, exercising it with a tiny canonical graph does not raise. This guards against future regressions when the underlying _call_..._for_parity helpers, __all__ ordering, or wrapper signatures drift.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-26T00:14:39.563161661Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T00:44:40.534764215Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T00:44:40.532912847Z","close_reason":"Shipped in cf0ff0d: 170-case smoke test covering all 80 OrangeHorse wrappers. All pass in 0.50s. Discovered upstream nx hang on strategy_saturation_largest_first(G, {}) with empty colors — worked around by exercising via greedy_color end-to-end instead.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-sgjko","title":"parity: time-respecting isomorphism matchers missing","description":"NetworkX exposes TimeRespectingGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta) and TimeRespectingDiGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta). FrankenNetworkX does not export these classes, leaving temporal VF2 matcher API unavailable. Add wrappers that convert FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegate to NetworkX, plus parity tests for signatures and isomorphism mappings on temporal graph/digraph paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:31:58.717555427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.565138940Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.563236879Z","close_reason":"Completed in 739ccaa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-uuo38","title":"parity: classes.filters hide_*/show_*/no_filter wrappers (11 fns)","description":"networkx.classes.filters exposes 11 filter factory functions used to construct subgraph views: hide_nodes(nodes), hide_edges(edges), hide_diedges(edges), hide_multiedges(edges), hide_multidiedges(edges), show_nodes(nodes), show_edges(edges), show_diedges(edges), show_multiedges(edges), show_multidiedges(edges), no_filter(*items). franken_networkx does not surface these. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__. Each returns a filter callable used by subgraph_view.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:49:38.907487801Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:04:39.857592364Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T23:04:39.855657558Z","close_reason":"Shipped in de44f96: 11 filter factory wrappers (hide_/show_ variants for nodes/edges/diedges/multiedges/multidiedges, plus no_filter). Verified including end-to-end subgraph_view(P5, filter_node=hide_nodes([2])) -> [0,1,3,4].","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
